6.10	Ruby_Blue	Ruby Blue	Ruby Blue were a UK folk rock/pop band of the late 1980s and early 1990s. Fronted by Rebecca Pidgeon, they released a total of four albums, beginning with Glances Askances in 1987 and Down From Above in 1990. The original members of the band were Rebecca and Roger Fife. Erika Spotswood and Anthony Coote later joined for the album Down From Above.	
